1
00:00:59,400 --> 00:00:59,960
Ladies and gentlemen,

2
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:00,560
welcome to

3
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:02,370
the Dragon Country Grand Prix!

4
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:16,940
Entering turn one.

5
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,840
Jing Chi from the Jiangnan team is indeed strong,

6
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:20,500
quickly taking back the lead.

7
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:22,200
Jaylen Brown of the Flame team

8
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,800
is closely tailing the Jiangnan team.

9
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:26,460
The competition between the two cars is fierce.

10
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:32,240
Jaylen Brown suddenly accelerates into the turn.

11
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:36,320
Jing Chi of the Jiangnan team crashed into Jaylen Brown,

12
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:38,720
and the Flame team's car hit the guardrail.

13
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,360
Jing Chi quickly shakes off Jaylen Brown,

14
00:01:44,360 --> 00:01:45,640
enters the leading group,

15
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:49,170
and starts competing with Shota Suzuki of the Supersonic team.

16
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:51,680
Both sides are very fast.

17
00:01:53,039 --> 00:01:54,560
Shota Suzuki attempts to overtake.

18
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,840
The Jiangnan team won't easily give up the first position.

19
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:58,900
The two continue to fiercely battle.

20
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:02,320
The Supersonic team is relentless in their pursuit,

21
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:04,440
and quickly overtakes the Jiangnan team to take first place.

22
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:06,770
The Lightning Dagger team drops to third.

23
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,440
Shota Suzuki of the Supersonic team has a style

24
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,320
that is extremely tough.

25
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:10,240
Jing Chi of the Jiangnan team

26
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:11,720
hasn't found an opportunity to overtake,

27
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:13,180
staying right on his tail.

28
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:13,720
What?

29
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:14,760
Jing Chi is actually

30
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:15,960
activating the drag reduction system on the curve,

31
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:16,880
going full speed!

32
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:18,680
This is an extremely risky move.

33
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:04,720
Zixi.

34
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,040
The leader of this Jiangnan team, He Nan,

35
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:08,440
he

36
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,600
was at the Senca Desert Race three months ago,

37
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,160
where he used a modified civilian car

38
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:12,800
to completely defeat three professional race cars.

39
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,240
Did you miss me?

40
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:15,450
He belongs to

41
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,360
the kind of people who have a natural affinity for the track.

42
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,160
It is said that

43
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,560
when he takes a corner,

44
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:23,220
the error of the vehicle can be controlled down to the centimeter.

45
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:06,120
The top three teams on the track right now

46
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,380
are the Jiangnan team,

47
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,660
the Supersonic team, and the Flame team.

48
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:11,000
Without a doubt.

49
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:11,360
Dragon Country Grand Prix Pragon.

50
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,480
Based on the past performances of these three teams,

51
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:15,210
I believe this year's champion

52
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,240
will still be the powerful

53
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:20,160
and two-time defending champion, Supersonic Team.

54
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,200
Don't speak too soon.

55
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,560
The strength of Jiangnan Team

56
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,360
should not be underestimated.

57
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,040
You mean...

58
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,280
with their car

59
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:27,400
modified with a second-hand engine?

60
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:28,560
If they win,

61
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:30,280
I'll take your last name.

62
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:32,000
Okay, if they win,

63
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,240
don't regret it.

64
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:37,000
Suzuki Shota is already leading in first place.

65
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,040
What you are seeing now

66
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:41,400
is the battle for second place between Jiangnan Team and Flame Team.

67
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:44,440
My goodness, it's like Mars colliding with Earth!

68
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:47,720
Jiangnan Team crashed!

69
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:53,020
Jaylen Brown lost control and flipped over!

70
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,980
Just admit defeat if you want to fight me.

71
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,280
Did I hear that right?

72
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:44,420
Jing Chi is driving a fake car.

73
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,260
How do you know?

74
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:49,240
I've had sensitive hearing since I was a child.

75
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,640
Any sound of a malfunction,

76
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:52,570
I know the cause as soon as I hear it.

77
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:54,490
Brother Nan,

78
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,400
you must have heard it wrong.

79
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:59,010
Jing Chi is not that kind of person.

80
00:05:59,159 --> 00:06:00,220
I trust my hearing.

81
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:01,680
Zixi.

82
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:05,120
I'm sorry.

83
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:11,160
The latest ranking of the Longguo Grand Prix.

84
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:11,440
Longguo Grand Prix Pragon.

85
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,320
Jiangnan Racing Team is now at the bottom.

86
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:14,320
Winning the championship in the third round

87
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:14,640
Winning the championship in the third round

88
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:15,900
is almost impossible.

89
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:17,360
You might not know this.

90
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,800
He Nan from the Jiangnan Racing Team

91
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:21,200
is the only racer who inherited his father's Eagle Eye.

92
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:21,880
Eagle Eye?

93
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,320
The so-called Eagle Eye means that

94
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:23,800
when the racer's car

95
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,840
when the racer's car

96
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:26,640
is at a constant speed,

97
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:28,000
from the racer's perspective,

98
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,000
everything outside the car slows down significantly.

99
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,640
If this racer is so amazing,

100
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,640
why isn't he on the track?

101
00:06:33,840 --> 00:06:35,520
Did he lose his nerve?

102
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,800
Usually, the best is saved for last.

103
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,760
Our Supersonic Team

104
00:06:48,159 --> 00:06:50,420
wants to win the championship this time.

105
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:55,159
Do us a favor.

106
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:29,610
Sorry, Captain.

107
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,060
In the second round of VOLSON,

108
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:37,360
Jingchi is not feeling well today.

109
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,690
He didn't perform well.

110
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:39,480
Right.

111
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,260
Everyone makes mistakes.

112
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:45,280
Don't.

113
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,560
Don't.

114
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:47,560
Enough.

115
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:51,400
My team doesn't welcome traitors.

116
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:53,520
Traitors?

117
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,180
What do you mean, Captain?

118
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,680
I told you to get lost.

119
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,800
Internal conflict already?

120
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:19,920
Your Jiangnan Racing Team is indeed overrated.

121
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:22,000
After racing like that the first time,

122
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,160
you still have the nerve to race a second time.

123
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:24,960
In my opinion,

124
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:27,600
you should just give up.

125
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:30,160
We just went easy on you in the first round.

126
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,200
It's no fun to win so easily.

127
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:35,240
You really don't know your place, kid.

128
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:37,400
Do you know who I am?

129
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:38,460
Who is that?

130
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:39,600
Who is he?

131
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:40,360
I don't know.

132
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,620
I don't recognize him.

133
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:42,679
His name is Suzuki Shota, Jiangnan.

134
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:43,120
His name is Suzuki Shota.

135
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,200
He is the champion of the last two tournaments.

136
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:44,680
Jiangnan.

137
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:46,040
His supersonic car, Flame,

138
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:48,000
is the best-performing race car on the Japanese market.

139
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:48,600
All right.

140
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:49,640
I got it.

141
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:52,720
The Japanese who is about to lose to me.

142
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,930
You overestimate your abilities.

143
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,260
How about this?

144
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,410
Let's make a bet.

145
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,440
Whoever loses

146
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,660
has to kneel down in front of everyone

147
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:04,440
and wipe the other's helmet. What do you think?

148
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:10,520
I'll play along to the end.

149
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:11,730
Captain.

150
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,320
Shiqi is right.

151
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:16,200
Our car's performance is not as good as theirs.

152
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:16,840
And we are already

153
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:18,120
52 seconds behind.

154
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,720
Why don't we just give up?

155
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,840
In my, He Nan's, racing team,

156
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,320
there is no such word as lose.

157
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:27,450
I like the challenge

158
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:29,140
of turning things around.

159
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,400
All right, He Nan.

160
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,120
I'd like to see

161
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,920
what you're going to use to beat me.

162
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:34,840
Can't you see?

163
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:39,200
Just this second-hand modified racing car,

164
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,400
it's more than enough

165
00:09:40,640 --> 00:09:41,960
to beat you.

166
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:00,880
Young man.

167
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:03,320
What car are you driving?

168
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:06,160
Windbreaker.

169
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,400
Windbreaker?

170
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:09,960
Trash car.

171
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:11,880
Hurry up and scrap it.

172
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:14,340
Do you think you are a world champion?

173
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:46,610
The race begins.

174
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:47,960
Suzuki Shota and the other drivers

175
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,960
stepped on the gas and took the lead.

176
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:50,640
No way.

177
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,080
What exactly happened?

178
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:53,320
Why hasn't Longguo's He Nan started?

179
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,360
Did he give up?

180
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,160
Hurry up,

181
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:55,880
Nan.

182
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:56,680
Hurry up.

183
00:10:58,720 --> 00:10:59,400
Hurry up!

184
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:07,000
Live broadcast.

185
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,120
The Jiangnan Team,

186
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:10,450
despite already being 52 seconds behind,

187
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,280
is giving a 10-second handicap.

188
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,400
Is he crazy?

189
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:14,400
Nan,

190
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,620
what's wrong with you?

191
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:19,280
Go!

192
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,800
Captain, are you kidding me?

193
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:22,320
If we don't start the car now, we really won't be able to catch up.

194
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:22,880
How about

195
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:25,300
we wave the white flag?

196
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:27,480
This isn't a race at all.

197
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:28,880
It's clearly a suicide mission.

198
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:29,360
Yeah.

199
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:31,080
I've commentated on so many races

200
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,520
and heard so many similar things.

201
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,120
In the end,

202
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:34,540
it's all just talk.

203
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:35,120
So,

204
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:37,360
this racer is either a genius

205
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:39,440
or a total failure.

206
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:40,680
Three years ago,

207
00:11:40,680 --> 00:11:42,200
my mother told me on her sickbed,

208
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:42,720
"Nan,

209
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,920
don't let regret drag you down."

210
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:46,840
Today,

211
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,160
I want everyone to know

212
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,640
that Jiangnan Team's craziness

213
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:56,480
is not recklessness,

214
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,530
but confidence.

215
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,840
Five seconds left.

216
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:05,480
The tires are spinning rapidly.

217
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,180
Could it be?

218
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:08,480
Is he pressurizing the tires?

219
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:12,880
Are you all ready to witness a miracle?
